1
00:00:30,552 --> 00:00:31,719
Inmate 1625!

2
00:00:32,303 --> 00:00:33,471
Hey! Get off him!

3
00:00:44,482 --> 00:00:45,650
Let's get you treated.

4
00:01:08,673 --> 00:01:10,466
The wound is quite deep.

5
00:01:10,550 --> 00:01:13,845
We'll have to keep an eye on him
as he continues his treatment.

6
00:01:13,928 --> 00:01:15,263
How is Min Ji-ung?

7
00:01:15,346 --> 00:01:18,266
He wasn't hurt.
We've separated him from the attacker.

8
00:01:18,349 --> 00:01:20,393
Notify me
once you've questioned the attacker.

9
00:01:32,197 --> 00:01:33,865
Ms. Choi

10
00:01:35,033 --> 00:01:37,702
was the only adult who was good to me.

11
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:42,081
And to such a teacher, I…

12
00:01:46,461 --> 00:01:49,255
I will live with remorse
for the rest of my life

13
00:01:49,339 --> 00:01:51,216
and repent until I die.

14
00:01:52,342 --> 00:01:56,387
I will not live a single moment
of my life in peace.

15
00:01:58,723 --> 00:02:00,099
I'm sorry.

16
00:02:06,397 --> 00:02:07,899
I'm sorry.

17
00:02:08,608 --> 00:02:09,984
I'm sorry.

18
00:02:10,485 --> 00:02:12,362
I'm truly sorry.

19
00:02:12,862 --> 00:02:15,073
I'm sorry.

20
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:51,985
<i>What are you, a saint?</i>

21
00:02:52,485 --> 00:02:55,405
You'd be a psychopath
if you didn't feel anything.

22
00:02:56,364 --> 00:02:57,615
What did I tell you?

23
00:02:57,699 --> 00:02:59,284
That you'd see Cho Gyu-cheol,

24
00:02:59,367 --> 00:03:03,246
and a fire would burn in your heart
and drive you crazy.

25
00:03:05,206 --> 00:03:07,583
It's a fire neither of us
can ever extinguish.

26
00:03:08,084 --> 00:03:09,836
I told you, you would have to decide.

27
00:03:09,919 --> 00:03:11,879
Whether to live as Ga-yun's fiancé

28
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:14,090
or as an ERPB inspector.

29
00:03:19,512 --> 00:03:20,513
You did well.

30
00:03:21,973 --> 00:03:23,057
Well done.

31
00:03:24,017 --> 00:03:25,977
Is that all you have to say?

32
00:03:27,145 --> 00:03:30,064
Do you want me to pat you on the head
and compliment you?

33
00:03:31,357 --> 00:03:32,400
Yes, please do.

34
00:03:33,443 --> 00:03:34,944
Get lost, you punk!

35
00:03:37,363 --> 00:03:38,531
Gosh.

36
00:03:39,324 --> 00:03:41,868
Let's go out tonight for some soju.

37
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:46,456
Why aren't you answering?

38
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:52,962
Living as Choi Gang-seok's son-in-law
wasn't one of the options.

39
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,216
Get out, you punk!

40
00:03:57,925 --> 00:03:58,926
You can walk!

41
00:03:59,427 --> 00:04:01,304
Come on, we're almost there.

42
00:04:01,387 --> 00:04:04,432
You never let anything go, do you? Jesus.

43
00:04:04,515 --> 00:04:07,935
All I'm saying is
that it wasn't one of the choices.

44
00:04:08,019 --> 00:04:09,979
-You're feeling guilty--
-But I admitted it!

45
00:04:12,648 --> 00:04:14,442
-You're here, sir.
-Hello, sir.

46
00:04:14,525 --> 00:04:15,860
Let's cut the greetings.

47
00:04:15,943 --> 00:04:17,695
How's the drug investigation going?

48
00:04:17,779 --> 00:04:20,490
We have officially requested cooperation
from the police,

49
00:04:20,573 --> 00:04:22,575
and we're searching schools
for hidden drugs.

50
00:04:22,658 --> 00:04:25,495
The official urine-test request form
for every school

51
00:04:25,578 --> 00:04:27,955
has been uploaded
for the full-scale investigation.

52
00:04:28,039 --> 00:04:29,332
And the gambling case?

53
00:04:29,832 --> 00:04:32,085
We're tracking
the gambling site's IP address.

54
00:04:32,168 --> 00:04:34,837
We've set it up to track them
through the loan sharks.

55
00:04:34,921 --> 00:04:36,172
This case is also serious.

56
00:04:36,255 --> 00:04:37,590
-Minister!
-Keep on top of it.

57
00:04:37,673 --> 00:04:41,177
-Minister!
-Sir, you can't act like this here.

58
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:43,179
-Minister!
-I said you can't do this.

59
00:04:43,262 --> 00:04:44,430
Please, Minister.

60
00:04:44,514 --> 00:04:48,226
You need to follow the procedure
to see the minister.

61
00:04:48,309 --> 00:04:50,770
Who cares about the procedure? Minister!

62
00:04:50,853 --> 00:04:52,730
-What's going on?
-Minister!

63
00:04:54,273 --> 00:04:56,067
Minister!

64
00:04:57,276 --> 00:05:00,113
Please just take a look at this.

65
00:05:03,324 --> 00:05:07,370
This is the damage report

66
00:05:07,954 --> 00:05:09,747
from my own investigation.

67
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:12,583
And

68
00:05:13,709 --> 00:05:14,544
these are

69
00:05:15,628 --> 00:05:16,921
formal complaints.

70
00:05:17,422 --> 00:05:18,423
Just a moment.

71
00:05:18,506 --> 00:05:19,841
One moment, please!

72
00:05:21,217 --> 00:05:23,386
And these are medical records.

73
00:05:23,469 --> 00:05:26,055
And this is… Just a moment.

74
00:05:26,139 --> 00:05:27,515
Where did it go?

75
00:05:29,767 --> 00:05:32,186
Please take a look at it.

76
00:05:33,146 --> 00:05:35,982
Please!

77
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:38,067
Please have a seat.

78
00:05:38,151 --> 00:05:39,861
-Please have a seat.
-Here.

79
00:05:42,196 --> 00:05:43,030
Here you are.

80
00:05:43,823 --> 00:05:44,991
Thank you.

81
00:05:57,170 --> 00:06:00,882
I have no one to talk to about this,

82
00:06:01,632 --> 00:06:03,217
and no one will listen.

83
00:06:03,801 --> 00:06:07,722
And it's not as if my son is innocent.

84
00:06:08,514 --> 00:06:10,016
You came to the right place.

85
00:06:10,641 --> 00:06:12,018
How can I help you?

86
00:06:17,899 --> 00:06:19,275
My punk of a son…

87
00:06:21,486 --> 00:06:25,448
Our sales for the third quarter increased
by 18% compared to last year.

88
00:06:25,531 --> 00:06:27,074
Our operating profit margin also…

89
00:06:27,158 --> 00:06:27,992
Hello?

90
00:06:28,075 --> 00:06:29,952
<i>You took your fucking time to answer.</i>

91
00:06:30,912 --> 00:06:32,747
<i>You're Lee Jae-yun's father, right?</i>

92
00:06:33,247 --> 00:06:34,999
-Look.
-<i>Fucking answer me.</i>

93
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:37,293
<i>I said answer me!</i>

94
00:06:37,793 --> 00:06:38,920
Who is this?

95
00:06:39,003 --> 00:06:41,088
<i>You don't need to know who I am.</i>

96
00:06:41,172 --> 00:06:43,174
<i>Just pay off your goddamn son's debt.</i>

97
00:06:48,137 --> 00:06:50,348
I played a game.

98
00:06:51,599 --> 00:06:52,683
A game?

99
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:54,352
Did you buy in-game items?

100
00:06:54,435 --> 00:06:56,604
How much do you owe exactly?

101
00:06:56,687 --> 00:06:59,148
Is it about 100,000 or 200,000 won?

102
00:07:00,149 --> 00:07:01,442
We're asking you!

103
00:07:01,526 --> 00:07:03,152
How much is the debt?

104
00:07:06,197 --> 00:07:09,367
About 85 million won…

105
00:07:11,911 --> 00:07:12,745
What?

106
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,665
Eighty-five million won?

107
00:07:15,748 --> 00:07:16,832
Oh my God.

108
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:18,543
Wait.

109
00:07:18,626 --> 00:07:20,628
What on earth did you do?

110
00:07:20,711 --> 00:07:22,630
What kind of game did you play?

111
00:07:48,364 --> 00:07:52,618
TEACH YOU A LESSON

112
00:07:54,537 --> 00:07:55,454
Jae-yun.

113
00:07:57,331 --> 00:07:58,541
Mom and Dad

114
00:07:59,667 --> 00:08:00,710
paid off your debt.

115
00:08:02,169 --> 00:08:04,005
Everyone makes mistakes.

116
00:08:04,088 --> 00:08:06,215
You just can't make the same one again.

117
00:08:07,091 --> 00:08:09,176
I'm sure Jae-yun will do better now.

118
00:08:09,677 --> 00:08:12,597
What matters is that you learn from this…

119
00:08:14,765 --> 00:08:15,933
and never do it again.

120
00:08:21,731 --> 00:08:22,565
Let's eat.

121
00:08:23,774 --> 00:08:24,775
Why are you crying?

122
00:08:30,197 --> 00:08:31,324
Don't cry.

123
00:08:31,907 --> 00:08:32,742
Don't cry.

124
00:08:44,754 --> 00:08:47,632
50,000 WON SIGN-UP BONUS
SURPRISE COUPON, CLICK NOW

125
00:09:03,773 --> 00:09:08,110
VIP GAME ROOM
UNLIMITED BONUS EVENT FOR A LIMITED TIME

126
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:18,245
You little punk!

127
00:09:18,871 --> 00:09:20,206
You punk!

128
00:09:20,289 --> 00:09:23,125
We only just paid off your debt,

129
00:09:23,209 --> 00:09:25,628
and you gamble again? You punk!

130
00:09:27,129 --> 00:09:30,132
-You little punk.
-Honey, please don't…

131
00:09:52,363 --> 00:09:54,407
Just read webtoons on this
when you're bored.

132
00:09:57,201 --> 00:09:58,285
I won't gamble.

133
00:09:59,161 --> 00:10:01,372
I'm going to read just one webtoon.

134
00:10:27,022 --> 00:10:28,357
It's all right.

135
00:10:28,441 --> 00:10:29,900
-Just a moment.
-Look.

136
00:10:29,984 --> 00:10:31,444
-Hold on.
-Your kid is in debt.

137
00:10:31,527 --> 00:10:34,071
That means you gotta pay it back.

138
00:10:36,407 --> 00:10:38,033
It's fine. Just stay seated!

139
00:10:38,117 --> 00:10:40,953
If your damn kid screws up,

140
00:10:41,036 --> 00:10:42,955
you take the beating for them.

141
00:10:48,502 --> 00:10:51,338
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

142
00:10:56,177 --> 00:10:57,303
I really need…

143
00:10:59,221 --> 00:11:01,557
my severance pay.

144
00:11:05,394 --> 00:11:06,437
<i>You see,</i>

145
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:09,315
I've tried everything I could.

146
00:11:12,151 --> 00:11:17,740
I put him on impulse-control medication
prescribed by a neuropsychiatrist.

147
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:22,953
I even went to see a shaman.

148
00:11:23,454 --> 00:11:26,373
I already reported it to the police
a long time ago.

149
00:11:26,457 --> 00:11:27,792
But they say

150
00:11:28,793 --> 00:11:30,628
they can't do anything.

151
00:11:30,711 --> 00:11:33,047
Even if you block
the gambling site's IP address,

152
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:35,758
all they have to do
is switch to a new one.

153
00:11:36,509 --> 00:11:41,347
There were
so many damn reviews and approvals.

154
00:11:41,931 --> 00:11:47,812
It took me six months
to get this paperwork done.

155
00:11:49,688 --> 00:11:52,233
And all the while,
time just kept slipping by.

156
00:11:52,316 --> 00:11:54,026
Please take a look at this.

157
00:11:55,027 --> 00:11:58,489
My son ran away from home.

158
00:12:00,032 --> 00:12:01,700
I don't even know if he's alive.

159
00:12:03,869 --> 00:12:06,247
I wasn't sure how to deliver this to you.

160
00:12:06,872 --> 00:12:08,624
I'm sorry, Minister!

161
00:12:08,707 --> 00:12:11,836
I'm not sure
how I should give this to you.

162
00:12:11,919 --> 00:12:13,170
I'm sorry.

163
00:12:13,254 --> 00:12:15,130
You don't have to say

164
00:12:16,465 --> 00:12:18,884
anything else to us.

165
00:12:24,348 --> 00:12:25,307
NAKWON HIGH SCHOOL

166
00:12:25,391 --> 00:12:26,475
<i>Everyone, say hello.</i>

167
00:12:26,559 --> 00:12:30,437
This is Bong Geun-dae, a new student
joining our class from today.

168
00:12:30,521 --> 00:12:31,355
Say hi.

169
00:12:32,356 --> 00:12:35,776
Hi, I'm Bong Geun-dae. I'm new here.

170
00:12:40,281 --> 00:12:42,825
Why don't you sit over there
in front of Seong-bin?

171
00:12:43,325 --> 00:12:45,953
Seong-bin,
have you heard from Jae-yun yet?

172
00:12:46,829 --> 00:12:49,081
-No.
-If you do, let me know right away.

173
00:12:49,164 --> 00:12:49,999
Okay.

174
00:12:50,082 --> 00:12:52,751
-Have a great day!
-Yes, ma'am!

175
00:12:56,213 --> 00:12:57,131
I won!

176
00:12:57,214 --> 00:12:58,257
I won again!

177
00:12:58,340 --> 00:12:59,425
How much did you win?

178
00:12:59,508 --> 00:13:01,093
-One million won.
-Bull!

179
00:13:01,176 --> 00:13:02,761
Look. It's for real.

180
00:13:04,430 --> 00:13:05,598
Another jackpot!

181
00:13:09,977 --> 00:13:10,978
-Too bad.
-Damn it.

182
00:13:12,187 --> 00:13:14,148
Fucking hell!

183
00:13:14,857 --> 00:13:16,066
I'm so done.

184
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,151
Yes, 200,000 won!

185
00:13:21,655 --> 00:13:25,034
Fuck, that was close.
My mom would've lost her shit.

186
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:26,911
-What?
-What?

187
00:13:28,454 --> 00:13:30,539
Goddamn it!

188
00:13:30,623 --> 00:13:33,208
What the hell are you staring at, dumbass?

189
00:13:33,876 --> 00:13:38,172
<i>They say online gambling</i>
<i>wouldn't survive without teenagers.</i>

190
00:13:39,298 --> 00:13:44,511
Our recent online gambling busts showed
that over 50% of their users were minors.

191
00:13:44,595 --> 00:13:47,014
There was even a 9-year-old. A 9-year-old!

192
00:13:47,097 --> 00:13:51,060
Loan sharks are always
around kids who gamble.

193
00:13:51,143 --> 00:13:52,978
-There--
-A few million won is nothing.

194
00:13:53,062 --> 00:13:56,023
Those kids owe hundreds of millions!
They owe…

195
00:13:56,106 --> 00:13:57,608
There have also been many cases

196
00:13:57,691 --> 00:14:00,235
where kids, like Jae-yun,
have run away from home.

197
00:14:00,319 --> 00:14:01,612
Gambling is one thing,

198
00:14:01,695 --> 00:14:03,697
but the related crimes
are just as serious.

199
00:14:03,781 --> 00:14:05,699
Most of it is to pay off debts.

200
00:14:05,783 --> 00:14:08,035
We will catch these punks.

201
00:14:08,118 --> 00:14:11,997
But we can't do it alone.
We'll need help from other departments.

202
00:14:12,081 --> 00:14:14,625
They say it takes a village
to raise a child.

203
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:17,586
The police, prosecutors, the MSIT,
and the Ministry of Justice

204
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:18,587
must all cooperate.

205
00:14:19,797 --> 00:14:23,592
If they refuse to,
I'll have to drag them in by the collar.

206
00:14:23,676 --> 00:14:26,303
But I think they're all higher up
in the chain than us.

207
00:14:26,387 --> 00:14:28,222
The kids' card wins hands down.

208
00:14:30,808 --> 00:14:32,017
Good day, sir.

209
00:14:40,275 --> 00:14:41,193
Where were you at?

210
00:14:41,777 --> 00:14:44,071
I came straight from home.

211
00:14:44,154 --> 00:14:46,281
Dumbass. Not that. Which school?

212
00:14:47,324 --> 00:14:48,283
Guun High.

213
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:50,202
I got it! Hell yeah!

214
00:14:50,285 --> 00:14:52,538
-What is it? Did you hit it big?
-Really?

215
00:14:52,621 --> 00:14:53,497
How much?

216
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:54,999
Fuck, it's a million won.

217
00:14:55,082 --> 00:14:56,125
-A million.
-A million?

218
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,544
-You might actually buy a motorcycle.
-What is that?

219
00:14:58,627 --> 00:15:00,379
I won, so dinner's on me tonight.

220
00:15:00,462 --> 00:15:02,798
Hey! Anyone up for some good food?

221
00:15:02,881 --> 00:15:04,967
Fuck, Seong-bin is buying today!

222
00:15:06,135 --> 00:15:07,761
I hit the jackpot, suckers!

223
00:15:07,845 --> 00:15:09,388
I want octopus <i>jjamppong</i>!

224
00:15:09,471 --> 00:15:10,806
-Seafood for me!
-Beef for me.

225
00:15:10,889 --> 00:15:12,725
-Sure.
-I'll have braised pork belly!

226
00:15:14,518 --> 00:15:17,104
Maybe black bean noodles?

227
00:15:17,938 --> 00:15:20,065
I'm all in on Banker until the run breaks.

228
00:15:20,149 --> 00:15:21,358
Hey, hold on.

229
00:15:21,442 --> 00:15:24,278
Trust me, let's bet on "tie."
The streak's gonna break.

230
00:15:24,361 --> 00:15:27,031
Don't you know not to trust anyone
going for a tie?

231
00:15:27,114 --> 00:15:29,241
You mean full house, not tie, you idiot.

232
00:15:29,324 --> 00:15:30,534
The Banker is drawing.

233
00:15:41,545 --> 00:15:43,172
What is it?

234
00:15:43,255 --> 00:15:44,590
Can you let me in too?

235
00:15:44,673 --> 00:15:46,050
I told you it's just a game.

236
00:15:46,633 --> 00:15:48,093
Isn't it like gambling?

237
00:15:48,177 --> 00:15:50,220
I saw you win money.

238
00:15:50,304 --> 00:15:51,764
Gambling is a scary thing.

239
00:15:51,847 --> 00:15:53,891
This is just a game. A money-making one.

240
00:15:54,641 --> 00:15:56,351
Don't you play with your own money?

241
00:15:56,435 --> 00:15:59,188
Who uses their own money?
You get a free bonus when you join.

242
00:15:59,271 --> 00:16:03,942
Seong-bin here flipped the free bonus
and bought an RTX 5090 Ti graphics card.

243
00:16:04,026 --> 00:16:06,278
-An RTX 5090 Ti? That's super expensive.
-Yeah.

244
00:16:06,361 --> 00:16:07,237
You can do it too.

245
00:16:08,405 --> 00:16:10,699
-Shall I show you?
-Yeah.

246
00:16:11,950 --> 00:16:12,993
If you sign up here

247
00:16:13,077 --> 00:16:15,871
and enter my ID for the referral,
you get an extra 50,000 won.

248
00:16:16,455 --> 00:16:17,414
Just a moment.

249
00:16:17,498 --> 00:16:19,500
Do I really get free money?

250
00:16:19,583 --> 00:16:20,793
For God's sake!

251
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:23,754
Give me that.

252
00:16:25,130 --> 00:16:27,591
First, sign up.

253
00:16:27,674 --> 00:16:29,676
Create your password.

254
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,928
And for the code…

255
00:16:31,762 --> 00:16:32,971
Hey, see that?

256
00:16:33,055 --> 00:16:34,348
You got 50,000 won.

257
00:16:34,431 --> 00:16:36,934
Since you don't know anything,
start with Odd or Even.

258
00:16:37,518 --> 00:16:38,727
-Odd or Even?
-Hurry.

259
00:16:38,811 --> 00:16:39,645
-Just pick.
-Pick.

260
00:16:39,728 --> 00:16:41,063
I'll go with odd.

261
00:16:41,146 --> 00:16:42,231
-Tap on it.
-Right.

262
00:16:46,568 --> 00:16:48,153
-This guy got it.
-Let's see.

263
00:16:48,237 --> 00:16:49,363
You've got the touch.

264
00:16:49,446 --> 00:16:50,531
Even.

265
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,202
<i>Hey, what the hell?</i>

266
00:16:55,702 --> 00:16:56,578
Here.

267
00:16:56,662 --> 00:16:59,706
This kid, who approached me first,
is the recruiter.

268
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:02,543
He's Seong-bin,
and he works with a few shills.

269
00:17:02,626 --> 00:17:05,212
At first, they say they've won big,

270
00:17:05,295 --> 00:17:08,132
getting you curious and interested.

271
00:17:08,215 --> 00:17:10,551
Then they exclude you
from the conversation.

272
00:17:10,634 --> 00:17:13,846
And if you don't gamble,
they isolate you like an outcast.

273
00:17:13,929 --> 00:17:17,015
They say "game" instead of "gambling."
It's less off-putting.

274
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:20,727
Is the next move
for Deputy Director Bong to lose money?

275
00:17:20,811 --> 00:17:23,355
But there's something I don't understand.

276
00:17:23,438 --> 00:17:26,024
Gambling is basically math.

277
00:17:26,108 --> 00:17:28,110
If you know middle school math

278
00:17:28,193 --> 00:17:30,612
and know how to apply statistics,

279
00:17:30,696 --> 00:17:33,657
it's a system where you can't lose money.

280
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:34,741
I see.

281
00:17:35,242 --> 00:17:36,076
Is that so?

282
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:39,079
You don't have to lose money on purpose.
Win if you can.

283
00:17:40,205 --> 00:17:42,875
