Victims?

786
00:52:45,475 --> 00:52:47,477
What about the parents

787
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:51,481
who lost their life savings and home
and even quit their jobs

788
00:52:52,565 --> 00:52:54,192
because of their kid's gambling?

789
00:52:56,695 --> 00:53:00,615
What about the father who's slapped
in public by someone half his age…

790
00:53:03,118 --> 00:53:05,829
<i>but still has to kneel and beg,</i>
<i>all because of his kid?</i>

791
00:53:11,418 --> 00:53:13,920
What about the mother
who scrubs greasy grills

792
00:53:14,004 --> 00:53:15,714
in the kitchen of a barbecue joint

793
00:53:15,797 --> 00:53:18,133
<i>because the father can't do anything else</i>

794
00:53:19,217 --> 00:53:20,218
<i>but watch their kid?</i>

795
00:53:26,016 --> 00:53:30,103
What about the father
who goes from the police to the ERPB,

796
00:53:30,603 --> 00:53:36,276
even while being looked down on
and treated like some peddler,

797
00:53:36,359 --> 00:53:40,488
begging and crying for his child
to be saved?

798
00:53:48,913 --> 00:53:49,873
Victims?

799
00:53:53,168 --> 00:53:55,211
They're the real victims.

800
00:54:01,551 --> 00:54:04,846
You had countless chances to stop.

801
00:54:06,181 --> 00:54:08,892
And you're the ones
who threw those chances away.

802
00:54:13,605 --> 00:54:17,650
Do you really want to quit gambling
and be forgiven by the people around you?

803
00:54:18,985 --> 00:54:20,945
Then admit you are perpetrators.

804
00:54:23,406 --> 00:54:25,992
Never stop reflecting on yourselves

805
00:54:27,243 --> 00:54:28,995
and never stop asking for forgiveness.

806
00:54:32,665 --> 00:54:34,626
This is your last chance.

807
00:55:01,694 --> 00:55:03,029
Here you go.

808
00:55:03,988 --> 00:55:05,407
It's hot, isn't it?

809
00:55:08,284 --> 00:55:09,244
Oscillate.

810
00:55:12,288 --> 00:55:14,457
You earn money through labor.

811
00:55:14,541 --> 00:55:16,835
There's no such thing
as a get-rich-quick scheme.

812
00:55:17,877 --> 00:55:19,921
Keep scrubbing.

813
00:55:20,004 --> 00:55:22,173
-Scrub your minds clean.
-You need more suds.

814
00:55:22,757 --> 00:55:23,925
Hand it over.

815
00:55:26,845 --> 00:55:28,596
That's it. Good.

816
00:55:30,974 --> 00:55:36,729
That means you now have
98,320,000 won left to pay your parents.

817
00:55:36,813 --> 00:55:39,065
You clean up your own mess.

818
00:55:39,149 --> 00:55:40,567
Oh, and…

819
00:55:43,361 --> 00:55:45,697
<i>To page, press one. To record a message…</i>

820
00:55:47,824 --> 00:55:48,783
Your pagers.

821
00:55:49,367 --> 00:55:50,201
4868253.

822
00:55:50,285 --> 00:55:51,828
Do you remember what this means?

823
00:55:51,911 --> 00:55:53,163
"I love you. Come quickly."

824
00:55:53,997 --> 00:55:54,831
Love you.

825
00:55:54,914 --> 00:55:58,168
Please give our phones back now.
We'll only make calls.

826
00:55:58,251 --> 00:56:00,336
What high schooler
would use this nowadays?

827
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:03,256
Freedom is only granted
when you take responsibility.

828
00:56:03,339 --> 00:56:04,883
And most importantly,

829
00:56:05,467 --> 00:56:07,260
I don't believe a gambler's word.

830
00:56:07,969 --> 00:56:09,137
I'll page you.

831
00:56:10,263 --> 00:56:12,056
337337.

832
00:56:12,557 --> 00:56:14,642
Oh man.

833
00:56:17,312 --> 00:56:18,354
It's really fine.

834
00:56:18,438 --> 00:56:21,608
After all, I'm the reason
your phone is broken.

835
00:56:21,691 --> 00:56:25,278
It's just the screen that's broken.
It's still usable.

836
00:56:27,363 --> 00:56:28,448
I just feel bad.

837
00:56:29,115 --> 00:56:31,951
I said I'd protect you, but I failed.

838
00:56:32,035 --> 00:56:33,495
So please, okay?

839
00:56:33,578 --> 00:56:36,164
Just pick one.
There are so many phones here.

840
00:56:36,247 --> 00:56:37,749
-Which is the latest?
-It's fine.

841
00:56:37,832 --> 00:56:38,666
Come on, pick one.

842
00:56:38,750 --> 00:56:40,084
-What's the latest--
-Oh?

843
00:56:41,336 --> 00:56:44,005
Then I'll just take a quick look.

844
00:56:45,173 --> 00:56:47,008
-Do you know this one?
-Yes.

845
00:56:47,091 --> 00:56:51,179
They changed the CPU on this model,
so the Internet should be really fast.

846
00:56:51,262 --> 00:56:52,347
-It's so cool.
-I see.

847
00:56:52,430 --> 00:56:53,264
Look.

848
00:56:53,348 --> 00:56:54,390
Right.

849
00:57:15,703 --> 00:57:17,330
Sir, can I please get a flip phone?

850
00:57:17,413 --> 00:57:19,207
-No, we don't need one.
-A flip phone.

851
00:57:19,874 --> 00:57:21,167
I'm not the addictive type.

852
00:57:21,251 --> 00:57:22,293
-Not anymore.
-Hello?

853
00:57:22,377 --> 00:57:24,963
-I'm bringing another addict, sir.
-I'm not an addict.

854
00:57:25,046 --> 00:57:26,297
-Sir, I'm not…
-Yes, sir.

855
00:57:26,381 --> 00:57:27,549
Goodbye.

856
00:57:27,632 --> 00:57:28,758
-Hwang Gi-tae!
-Hello.

857
00:57:28,841 --> 00:57:30,051
One, two.

858
00:57:30,134 --> 00:57:34,847
Hwang Gi-tae!

859
00:57:34,931 --> 00:57:36,808
-Your shop is…
-Life is so tough.

860
00:57:36,891 --> 00:57:37,809
-Here.
-Thank you.

861
00:57:37,892 --> 00:57:38,851
<i>In the latest poll,</i>

862
00:57:38,935 --> 00:57:42,480
<i>Minister Choi Gang-seok</i>
<i>surpassed 50% approval for the first time,</i>

863
00:57:42,564 --> 00:57:46,442
<i>outpacing opposition leader Hwang Gi-tae</i>
<i>by 17%.</i>

864
00:57:46,526 --> 00:57:49,737
<i>Whether Minister Choi Gang-seok</i>
<i>will enter the presidential race…</i>

865
00:57:49,821 --> 00:57:52,156
-Well, then.
-Please look out for us.

866
00:57:52,240 --> 00:57:53,074
Thank you.

867
00:57:53,157 --> 00:57:54,367
This way, please.

868
00:57:54,450 --> 00:57:56,452
-Thank you for treating us, sir.
-Thank you.

869
00:57:57,078 --> 00:57:58,246
All right.

870
00:57:59,330 --> 00:58:01,207
I see you're already out campaigning.

871
00:58:02,208 --> 00:58:04,252
-Choi Gang-seok?
-Choi Gang-seok?

872
00:58:04,335 --> 00:58:05,962
-Why is he here?
-Have a seat.

873
00:58:06,045 --> 00:58:07,463
I'm a regular here. Great food.

874
00:58:08,464 --> 00:58:10,842
Ma'am, can I get another <i>tang </i>here?

875
00:58:10,925 --> 00:58:13,052
Just a moment, please.

876
00:58:24,939 --> 00:58:28,818
Why are you visiting the markets
before even registering as a candidate?

877
00:58:29,485 --> 00:58:31,904
Isn't that something you do
while campaigning?

878
00:58:32,405 --> 00:58:34,949
-This looks delicious.
-Yes, it's good.

879
00:58:36,451 --> 00:58:38,286
Minister Choi Gang-seok, have you heard?

880
00:58:38,369 --> 00:58:39,495
Oh, right.

881
00:58:40,413 --> 00:58:42,832
People don't really hear
the things said about them.

882
00:58:45,585 --> 00:58:47,962
I heard rumors in Yeouido.

883
00:58:49,756 --> 00:58:52,550
You're using your dead daughter
to make a run for president.

884
00:58:53,843 --> 00:58:56,012
They say politics is heartless.

885
00:59:10,401 --> 00:59:12,445
You're all ears when it's about others.

886
00:59:13,029 --> 00:59:16,115
I hear the Mirae Daehan Party
is holding an emergency meeting today.

887
00:59:18,326 --> 00:59:19,786
I guess you weren't told.

888
00:59:20,286 --> 00:59:22,330
I wonder what they need to discuss

889
00:59:23,581 --> 00:59:25,583
that they didn't tell you about.

890
00:59:29,045 --> 00:59:31,881
Could they be planning
to replace their presidential candidate

891
00:59:31,964 --> 00:59:34,801
because your approval ratings
are dropping?

892
00:59:39,847 --> 00:59:41,224
<i>Whose idea was this?</i>

893
00:59:41,307 --> 00:59:43,518
I'll head over
to the conference room right now.

894
00:59:45,186 --> 00:59:47,814
I'm the Mirae Daehan Party leader!

895
00:59:47,897 --> 00:59:49,315
Who's going to stop me?

896
00:59:51,401 --> 00:59:52,402
What is it?

897
00:59:54,529 --> 00:59:56,197
Sir, you have a visitor.

898
00:59:56,280 --> 00:59:58,324
Do I look like I want company right now?

899
00:59:58,908 --> 01:00:01,119
He has something to tell you
about the ERPB.

900
01:02:07,870 --> 01:02:10,832
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

